title: Boys Cross Country Roundup:Harding takes seventh
text:
Boys Cross Country Roundup:Harding takes seventh Marion Star staff report 3:21 p.m. EDT October 10, 2015 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Harding Invitational 
Marion Harding was seventh at the Harding Invitational (190 points), led by Roberto Oswald (14th, 16:44), Joseph Tinnerello (44th, 17:51), Brandon Keller (46th, 17:54), Colby Carter (48th, 17:56) and Zach Lingo (50th, 17:58). 
Northmor was ninth (257 points), led by Spencer Adams (29th, 17:19), James Walker (59th, 18:16), Alec Moore (62nd, 18:23), Chase Hoover (63rd, 18:25) and Mostyn Evans (70th, 18:37). 
Ridgedale was twelfth (344 points), led by Cole Brown (41st, 17:48), Clayton Baughman (81st, 19:01), Duvan Bautista (82nd, 19:04), Austin Hernandez (100th, 20:08) and Byron Fown (108th, 21:53). 
Pleasant was thirteenth (390 points), led by Doug Sabo (84th, 19:07), Korey Peltier (88th, 19:20), Josh Whaley (91st, 19:31), Nick Kimmel (97th, 19:52) and Kai Meade (110th, 23:18). 
Leading runners for River Valley were Jordan Parish (69th, 18:36), Josh Rivers (104th, 20:52) and Jake Montgomery (114th, 25:48). 
Mount Gilead Thill Invitational 
Buckeye Valley was second at the Mount Gilead Thill Invitational (61 points), led by Zach Kreft (1st, 15:39), Gavin Shearer (7th, 17:13), Nathan Holst (13th, 17:50), Nathan Heiser (16th, 18:02) and Jacob Zinn (27th, 18:46). 
Mount Gilead was third (66 points), led by Austin Hallabrin (2nd, 16:15), Casey White (10th, 17:36), Nick Weiss (14th, 17:53), Kyle Ciballi (17th, 18:11) and Kyle White (24th, 18:37). 
Cardington-Lincoln waas fourth (84 points), led by Jacob Long (5th, 16:34), Josh Queener (8th, 17:20), Mike Queener (11th, 17:45), Quin Maceyko (30th, 18:55) and Greg Osborne (52nd, 20:10). 
Elgin was fifth (151 points), led by Pablo Salinas (9th, 17:35), Aaron Poling (36th, 19:21), Jacob Poling (38th, 19:26), Kevin Conroy (58th, 20:36) and Seldon Dyer (91st, 23:20). Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1Lo9Fcp More Stories
